{"type":"message","id":"40193a05","parentId":"12a48073","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:43:31.046Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gw3qzfv7s05a_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 144141\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/hybrid_scoring_test.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- CFI Compression Experiment completed with key findings\r\n- Next experiment is pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n- The formula to test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clear: run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. This is a concrete, specific next step that advances the compression research.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's needed:\r\n1. Need to implement the hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Run on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n3. Compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe best action would be to either:\r\n1. Create the experiment script/implementation\r\n2. Update the research document with the experiment plan\r\n3. Implement the hybrid scoring in the existing analysis\r\n\r\nGiven the goal of \"be specific, prefer file edits\", I should update a relevant file that sets up or documents this experiment. The most logical next file to edit would be to update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the experiment design, or create a new experiment file.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending action more carefully, I should implement and run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. Let me create a concrete experiment plan/implementation file.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what file would be best to edit:\r\n1. `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md` - could add experiment details\r\n2. Create a new experiment script\r\n\r\nThe most impactful single action would be to implement the hybrid scoring formula and document the experiment design. Let me create an experiment specification file or update the synthesis document.\r\n\r\nActually, I should look at what would directly advance the pending experiment. The most concrete action would be to implement the scoring function and run the comparison. Let me create an experiment script or update the synthesis with the experiment plan.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a structured experiment approach to test the hybrid scoring method systematically.\r\n\r\nI'll design a comprehensive experiment that:\r\n- Generates a clear experimental framework\r\n- Defines precise evaluation metrics\r\n- Outlines data preprocessing steps\r\n- Establishes baseline comparison methods\r\n- Documents expected outcomes and analysis techniques\r\n\r\nThe experiment will provide a rigorous test of the proposed scoring formula, ensuring reproducible and insightful results that can advance the compression research.\r\n\r\nKey steps involve creating a detailed experiment script with:\r\n- Clear hypothesis testing\r\n- Statistical validation\r\n- Transparent methodology\r\n- Reproducible implementation\r\n\r\nThe goal is to transform the current heuristic approach into a well-defined, measurable experiment that offers clear insights into the scoring method's effectiveness.\r\n\r\nI'll design an experiment specification that captures the nuanced scoring strategy, focusing on precise mathematical modeling and empirical validation. The script will translate the conceptual formula into a computational framework that can systematically evaluate performance.\r\n\r\nThe primary objective is developing a rigorous experimental approach that quantifies the scoring mechanism's predictive power, moving beyond initial intuition toward evidence-based refinement.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring formula (Strategy C) as the next experiment, but there's no implementation or experiment script yet. I need to implement this concrete experiment to validate whether score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) distinguishes constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid scoring experiment script that implements the formula and runs the 80/20 split comparison on 200 pulses.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** RUNNING\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 BUT capped at freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33 → min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 → score = 1.0\r\n- Favor research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → moderate score based on both dimensions\r\n- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" from \"Phase 1\" based on frequency normalization\r\n\r\n### Formula Implementation\r\n```python\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\r\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\r\n    return cfi * freq_normalized\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Token Scoring Examples\r\n| Token | CFI | Freq | freq/120 | Hybrid Score | Classification |\r\n|-------|-----|------|----------|--------------|----------------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.33→1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\r\n| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 1.13→1.0 | 0.96 | Trajectory (allow) |\r\n| \"research\" | 0.75 | 80 | 0.67 | 0.50 | Trajectory (allow) |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 0.60 | 40 | 0.33 | 0.20 | Trajectory (allow) |\r\n\r\n### Key Insight\r\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps the frequency contribution, so even freq=160 tokens score at most 1.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:42:02\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774377811043}}
