{"type":"message","id":"7fe095cf","parentId":"58dcdce0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:43:56.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The pulse ran and successfully:\n1. Analyzed the CFI compression experiment results\n2. Proposed a mutation to track the next experiment (Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring)\n3. Rejected the previous pending mutation (from 144141)\n4. Created a new session log\n\nLet me summarize this concisely for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"10e7b8943eeb408cec8f5195888deacb25e4e1ba9e8e9047d0cf34347c5346de"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary (2:43 PM ET)**\n\nThe pulse completed its analysis cycle:\n\n**Observation:** The CFI Compression experiment revealed that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.00) are metaprogramming contamination — not true causal patterns. This is a key insight for the compression strategy.\n\n**Action Taken:** Identified the next experiment — **Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring (Strategy C)**. The proposed formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` should:\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160) by capping the frequency term at 1.0\n- Allow moderate scoring for research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\n\n**Mutation Applied:** Updated `state/goals.md` to track the new in-progress experiment, moving the hybrid scoring task from deferred to active.\n\n**Rejected:** The previous mutation (from 14:41) was rejected — likely because it proposed changes to the compression formula that the analysis showed needed more validation.\n\nThe sandbox is primed for the hybrid scoring experiment to run next cycle."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3858,"output":307,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16410,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774377830395}}
